##How to evaluate the merits and demerits of Wuhan's "City closure" in an article written by the CDC

The merits and demerits of the "city closure" in Wuhan have been evaluated variously at home and abroad.

The foreign media represented by the New York Times gave him a lot of negative comments. The argument goes that while these measures can help limit the spread of the virus to some extent, the huge social and economic costs, particularly panic and a run on medical resources, are enormous. Nature also quoted University of Queensland Virologists as saying the closure would turn Wuhan into a giant Petri dish where everyone would infect each other, creating more cases.

The World Health Organization (WHO) also has different voices. Trying to close down a city of 11m people is a new science, says Takariki, its representative in China. Such public health measures are unprecedented, and it is hard to say whether they will work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo | the China Standard Time held a news conference in Beijing at 7:30 p.m. on Feb. 24.

On February 17, Chinese CDC researchers published in the Chinese Journal of Preventive Medicine an overview of containment strategies in the early stage of the COVID-19.

The article holds that, on the whole, the implementation of containment measures has reduced the risk of continuous community transmission in other regions of China except Wuhan, delayed the arrival of the epidemic peak, and eased the pressure on medical resources, in order to prepare for a possible serious epidemic, precious time has been bought, but it has also had a certain impact on people's lives and social production in the heavily affected areas such as Wuhan, resulting in huge economic and social costs.

The corresponding author is Ruzhao Feng, a researcher in the Infectious Disease Management Office of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention. The authors, all but one from Nanning's Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, have signed up to 20 people.

Containment strategy of WHO endorsement

Quarantine laws originated in Italy and were first enacted by the 1370 in Venice to prevent the black death. Containment was proposed by WHO in 2005 as a guiding strategy for pandemic prevention and control, Feng and others point out in their paper. The strategy is to use both medical and non-medical intervention strategies and measures (area closures, school suspensions and work stoppages) within a defined geographical area to rapidly halt the spread of the disease in the early Emerging Infectious Diseases of the epidemic.

On January 23, Wuhan announced that the city-wide Lihan pass was temporarily closed. At this time for the initial transmission of the virus, imported cases in other areas have not yet caused widespread community transmission, experts still judge the possibility of containment of the epidemic in Hubei and other limited areas. It was during the peak travel season for Chinese New Year, and containment strategies were being implemented in areas such as Wuhan where there was community transmission, with a view to containment of the epidemic in limited areas such as Wuhan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | strategies and core measures for early containment of COVID-19 pneumonia in China. (Source: Chinese Journal of Preventive Medicine)

The core measures of the strategy include cordoning off epidemic areas, strengthening case isolation and close contact management, and reducing the movement of people (traffic control and travel restrictions, etc.) , increase Interpersonal Distance (cessation of large-scale activities, delayed opening of schools, delayed return to work in factories) and promote personal prevention among the public.

These measures are applied across the country, but Wuhan has gone to extremes in detecting and isolating cases. Since February 5, Wuhan has been converting public spaces into a shelter hospital, which aims to isolate and treat large numbers of people with mild illnesses in a short period of time and is based on a community grid, to take the door-to-door investigation and self-examination self-report combined approach, the implementation of the nationwide network-type investigation, "should be investigated, should be collected, should be treated as a cure" goal.

The tracking and management of close contacts is national. With the increase in the number of confirmed and reported cases of death, the community level nationwide began to implement grid-based, carpet-based management, focusing on tracking and urging people from the epidemic area of Wuhan, Home Medical Observation for 14 days, report any abnormal situation in time and take corresponding preventive and control measures to prevent the importation of epidemic situation. As the number of outbreaks has increased, since February 2, some provinces and cities, such as Tianjin, Shandong, Gansu, Nanjing, and Yunnan, have required all close contacts to go to designated places for medical observation, no longer take home quarantine, to prevent the spread of the epidemic.

The main measures to increase interpersonal distance are reducing public gatherings, delaying the resumption of work by enterprises, delaying the opening of schools, extending the Spring Festival holidays and managing urban and rural communities.

The management of urban and rural communities is becoming more and more strict. On 26 January, all localities were required to exercise strict control over their communities and villages, to close roads in their villages and to set up dissuasive points at the entrances and exits of residential areas and villages, and not to go out in principle except for medical treatment and necessary work and living needs; from 2 February, except for Wuhan, the vast majority of residential areas throughout the country are gradually under closed management, with one to two entrances and exits reserved according to the size of the area, and all other passageways closed, non-resident vehicles and personnel are not allowed to enter; some residents require one family member to be appointed at regular intervals to go out and purchase living materials on the basis of good protection measures.

Containment geometry

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | the epidemic curve of new coronary pneumonia in China. (Source: World Health Organization)

Feng and others acknowledge that while the World Health Organization has proposed similar strategies for pandemic influenza control, they are difficult to implement in many countries. They believe that China has the advantage of implementing a containment strategy because of its experience in dealing with the Emerging Infectious Diseases, multi-sectoral coordination under the guidance of the government, the active response of the public, and the response to the 2003 SARS and 2009 influenza pandemics.

Studies have suggested that case isolation, travel restrictions, increased interpersonal distance and personal protective measures taken by Wuhan in the early stages of the epidemic can effectively reduce the number of infections and deaths, without any core measures of containment strategies, there will be an order of magnitude difference in the final number of cases compared with the current number in Wuhan as of February 4.

Travel restrictions in different parts of the country could delay the spread of the new coronavirus from Wuhan to other cities by 2.9 days, a study says. Another study said that at this stage, a seven-day travel restriction in Beijing (no exposed people enter) can reduce the number of infected people by 91% .

Feng Luzhao and others believe that on the whole, the implementation of containment measures has reduced the risk of continuous community transmission in other areas of the country besides Wuhan, delayed the arrival of the epidemic peak, and eased the pressure on medical resources, this has bought valuable time to respond to a potentially serious epidemic.

However, the paper also admitted that the "closed city" on the Wuhan People's lives and social production caused a certain impact on economic and social costs. A large number of cases due to isolation treatment, close contacts concentrated isolation observation, on their families caused certain losses and impact, it is recommended that local governments consider giving certain social support, providing necessary services and relief, to ensure that the basic livelihood of vulnerable groups such as the elderly, the lonely, the sick, the disabled, the pregnant and those without a fixed income is not seriously affected.

The paper warned that special attention should also be paid to the prevention and control of the epidemic in nursing homes, welfare homes, apartments and other services, to ensure the supply of medical supplies, and to strengthen protective measures to prevent outbreaks in such institutions.

The authorities in Wuhan were negligent. According to a report by Caixin, the Wuhan Social Welfare home is only a few hundred meters from the south China Seafood Market. It was crowded with 19 deaths between December 2019 and February 2020. In addition to one death after a new crown was confirmed, six elderly people died of lung infections, there were many cases of infectious shock, acute myocardial infarction, sudden death and Arrhythmia, but there were many cases of fever.

The paper points out that considering the cost effect of the implementation of the strategy and measures, we can adjust and optimize the existing prevention and control measures as soon as possible, carry out the precise measures, and formulate the classification guidance prevention and control strategies of different regions and different epidemic levels and characteristics.

What did the WHO say

At a Feb. 24 news conference, Bruce Aylward, a foreign leader of the china-who Joint Expert Study Group on new coronary pneumonia and a senior adviser to the WHO Director-general, said, the Wuhan Mode and the Hubei mode are a special mode in the Chinese mode, which are suitable for the areas where the community communication occurs.

According to Science, the team concluded in an unpublished report of its visit that China's epidemic peaked between January 23 and February 2, and that China's aggressive containment efforts in Hubei province, at least 50m people are under a "home blockade" , buying valuable time for other Chinese provinces to fight the epidemic and ultimately preventing thousands of cases. The report also suggests that other countries must learn from the experience of this blockade. It does not have to be a total blockade, but equally stringent measures should be taken.

The science report quoted Laurence Gostin, an expert on global health policy at the Georgetown University Law Center, as saying China's domestic restrictions have taken a heavy toll on many individuals, the policies are "shocking, unprecedented and primitive, " and he said he was particularly concerned about the physical and mental health of people in Hubei Province who are confined to their homes, under close supervision and facing a shortage of medical services.

Liang Wannian, the Chinese leader of the Joint Expert Study Group and the Expert Group leader of the National Health Commission's response to the new coronavirus epidemic, said that the new coronavirus is very cunning, and we can not use existing knowledge to deal with it, we need to stop the epidemic, sum up the experience and change the measures and strategies. "Our early understanding of disease was inadequate, and that was our limitation, " he admits

For the next step in Wuhan, Liang Wannian suggested that all efforts should be made to strengthen prevention and control measures in Wuhan. On the one hand, they should strengthen prevention and control measures, and on the other hand, they should also diagnose patients, close contacts of patients, suspected patients as soon as possible, and identify all close contacts, management and treatment, which is the fundamental way to prevent new cases.

"We need to recognize the contribution of the people of Wuhan, and the World Owes you, " Bruce Aylward said. "I want to take this opportunity to thank the people of Wuhan once again on behalf of the world when this epidemic is over. "
